dikeri, Karnataka: 571201. 3. Omkareshwara Temple: The Omkareshwara temple is surrounded by a tranquil environment, Purest Spirituality, and beautiful scenery. In front of the temple is a cute lake where visitors enjoy feeding the fish. Lord Shiva is honoured at this temple. This magnificent temple is a wonderful example of architecture. The temple and its surroundings are exceptionally well kept and are part of a vast structure. A beautiful location for peace and meditation. Address: Stuart Hill, State Highway 88, Madikeri, Coorg, Karnataka, 571201. 4. Abbey Falls: See the Wonder of Nature, and One of the top attractions in Madikeri is Abbey Falls. Many people visit this spectacular, stunning waterfall. This fall's surroundings are kept up beautifully, and nearby parking and restrooms are also easily accessible. The waterfall is beautiful, and the surrounding region is very stunning. Near the waterfall, there is a nice bridge as well. To see this natural wonder, one would have to descend. During the monsoon season, the entire location, including the waterfall, appears rather bizarre. This is a must-see destination close to Madikeri. The address is Abbey Falls Road in Hebbettageri, Karnataka, 57120. 5. Raja's Tomb: Take pleasure in the royal architecture. King and royal tombs from the Kodava kingdom are in this unique location. The mausoleum has a highly attractive design and architecture and is located in an enticing landscape. One of Karnataka's most picturesque historical sites, it offers excellent views of the hills. From here, you'll enjoy a beautiful perspective of the Coorg region. The style of the architecture is influenced by Indian beautiful architecture. There are two important tombs in this area, and both were constructed in the first half of the 19th century. If you love history, you must visit this location in Madikeri. The address is SH27, Mahadevpet, Madikeri, Karnataka 571201. 6. Mandalpatti: In The Heart of Nature Due to the breathtaking beauty of 