ee this natural wonder, one would have to descend. During the monsoon season, the entire location, including the waterfall, appears rather bizarre. This is a must-see destination close to Madikeri. The address is Abbey Falls Road in Hebbettageri, Karnataka, 57120. 5. Raja's Tomb: Take pleasure in the royal architecture. King and royal tombs from the Kodava kingdom are in this unique location. The mausoleum has a highly attractive design and architecture and is located in an enticing landscape. One of Karnataka's most picturesque historical sites, it offers excellent views of the hills. From here, you'll enjoy a beautiful perspective of the Coorg region. The style of the architecture is influenced by Indian beautiful architecture. There are two important tombs in this area, and both were constructed in the first half of the 19th century. If you love history, you must visit this location in Madikeri. The address is SH27, Mahadevpet, Madikeri, Karnataka 571201. 6. Mandalpatti: In The Heart of Nature Due to the breathtaking beauty of the surrounding region, Mandalpatti Hills in Mahadevpet are amazing and mesmerizing. This is a fantastic location because it is right in the middle of nature. The cliffs are draped with evergreen forests that reach the skies. The full view from these cliffs is just stunning. This area occasionally experiences cloudiness and fog, which increases the atmosphere significantly. The address 571219 Mahadevpet, Madikeri, Karnataka. 7. Government Museum: The museum is a must-see attraction in Madikeri and is located inside the fort. Fascinating relics and old sculptures may be seen throughout this amazing museum. The museum is home to several fascinating statues of old gods and goddesses. This excellent museum has no entrance charge. The address is Stuart Hill in Madikeri, Karnataka 571201. 8. Kootu Poley Dam: A charming small dam with beautiful scenery is called Kootu Poley Dam. The area around the dam is gorgeous. This is a wonderful location tha